<br />

<div style="text-align: center;">
  <b><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">It is estimated that more than
  </span>
</b></div>

<div style="text-align: center;">
  <b><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">10,000 business books
  </span>
</b></div>

<div style="text-align: center;">
  <span style="font-family: arial;">
    <span style="font-size: large;"><b>are published each year.</b>
    </span>
    
    <span style="font-size: x-small;">
      <br />
    </span>
  
    <span style="font-size: medium;">
      <span style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial;"><br />source:&nbsp;
      </span>

      <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/michaelparrishdudell/2014/09/03/get-your-business-book-published-crown-publishing-group-editor-matt-inman-reveals-how/" style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #7d181e; font-family: arial; text-decoration-line: none;" target="_blank">Forbes</a></span></span><br />
</div>

<div style="font-family: arial;">
  <span style="font-size: large;">
    <br />
    Eleven books catapulted to the top in this year's search for the Best Business Books of 2012. For the fifth year running Beantown Web has conducted a quasi-scientific meta-search to identify the best business books published in the previous year.
    <br />
    <br />
    <span style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333;">This year's search began by identifying 10 "Best of" lists. This resource list is available upon request. Presented here are the results.
      <br />
      <br />
    </span>
  </span>
</div>

<div style="font-family: arial;">
  <span style="font-size: large;">A total of 63 books were mentioned on at least one "Best of" list. These 63 books comprise the <b>Honorable Mention</b> list.
  </span>
</div>

